		<title type="html"><![CDATA[IRCS Prosody Workshop 1992: Undoing bit rot]]></title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll/?p=48650&#038;utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=ircs-prosody-workshop-1992-undoing-bit-rot" />

		<id>https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll/?p=48650</id>
		<updated>2020-10-04T12:06:00Z</updated>
		<published>2020-10-04T09:31:22Z</published>
		<category scheme="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll" term="Linguistic history" /><category scheme="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll" term="Links" /><category scheme="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll" term="Prosody" />
		<summary type="html"><![CDATA[Recently, Antônio Simões wrote to Cynthia McLemore to ask about a 28-year-old proceedings: I used to find on the internet the Proceedings from 1992 that you edited with Mark Liberman. I tried to find them, but they are not on the internet anymore. Do you still have that volume in pdf? Or is it accessible [&#8230;]]]></summary>

					<content type="html" xml:base="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll/?p=48650&#038;utm_source=rss&#038;utm_medium=rss&#038;utm_campaign=ircs-prosody-workshop-1992-undoing-bit-rot"><![CDATA[<p>Recently, <a href="https://spanport.ku.edu/ant%C3%B4nio-r-m-simoes" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Antônio Simões</a> wrote to Cynthia McLemore to ask about a 28-year-old proceedings:</p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><span style="color: #000080;">I used to find on the internet the Proceedings from 1992 that you edited with Mark Liberman. I tried to find them, but they are not on the internet anymore. Do you still have that volume in pdf? Or is it accessible somewhere on the internet? This is the volume:</span></p>
<p style="padding-left: 40px;"><span style="color: #000080;">McLemore, Cynthia, and Mark Liberman, eds. 1992. Proceedings of the IRCS Workshop on Prosody in Natural Speech. IRCS Report No. 92-37.</span></p>
<p>"IRCS" stands for "Institute for Research in Cognitive Science", an NSF research center founded in 1990 by <a href="https://www.sas.upenn.edu/~gleitman/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lila Gleitman</a> and <a href="https://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/nll/?p=36048" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Aravind Joshi</a>. IRCS  died in 2016 after a lingering siege of academic politics, and its <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20190701000000*/http://www.ircs.upenn.edu" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">website seems to have been purged last year</a>. Penn's library has <a href="https://repository.upenn.edu/ircs_reports/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">some IRCS technical reports in its repository</a>, but not the one that Antônio is looking for. Many others are clearly missing, along with event recordings and so on &#8212; I'll see whether there are backups somewhere from which things can be restored.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, Cindie found a paper copy of the requested proceedings, and <a href="http://languagelog.ldc.upenn.edu/myl/IRCS_Prosody1992/TableOfContents.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">this page</a> provides a table of contents with links and abstracts for scanned versions of the 26 papers it contains. Most of them are still interesting and relevant today!</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content>
		
